HEADWORD: Decagon
<hw>Dec"a*gon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>deca-</ets> + Gr. <grk>gwni`a</grk> a corner or angle: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧cagone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A plane
figure having ten sides and ten angles; any figure having ten angles. A
<xex>regular decagon</xex> is one that has all its sides and angles
equal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

